1
00:00:05,690 --> 00:00:08,080
Hey, you guys. Hey, what are you doing?

2
00:00:08,130 --> 00:00:09,860
Figuring out our wedding plans.

3
00:00:09,910 --> 00:00:11,890
Funny. We were doing the same thing.

4
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:17,850
It's really crazy. The hall, the dress, the food.

5
00:00:17,900 --> 00:00:20,440
I had no idea how expensive this was.

6
00:00:20,490 --> 00:00:21,700
Yeah, it is really pricey.

7
00:00:21,750 --> 00:00:23,590
I freaked when I heard the numbers.

8
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:25,080
So, what did you two do about it?

9
00:00:25,080 --> 00:00:26,460
It was simple.

10
00:00:26,510 --> 00:00:28,590
I came up with some cost-cutting solutions...

11
00:00:28,640 --> 00:00:31,310
...wrote out a list, and Monica told me to go to hell.

12
00:00:32,710 --> 00:00:34,130
There's no way around it.

13
00:00:34,180 --> 00:00:36,930
Just accept that this is gonna cost a lot of money.

14
00:00:36,980 --> 00:00:40,440
I heard that weddings are, like, a $40 billion-a-year industry.

15
00:00:40,490 --> 00:00:43,290
Yeah. And I'm responsible for just, like, half of that.

16
00:00:45,550 --> 00:00:49,120
But really, it does seem like this money could be put to better use.

17
00:00:49,120 --> 00:00:50,400
Are you serious?

18
00:00:50,450 --> 00:00:52,120
Yeah. How would you feel

19
00:00:52,170 --> 00:00:53,870
if we gave all the wedding money to charity...

20
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:56,290
...and we just got married at City Hall?

21
00:00:56,340 --> 00:00:59,080
I think it would make me wanna marry you even more.

22
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:04,860
I gotta say, you guys, that's an incredible gesture.

23
00:01:04,910 --> 00:01:07,050
Maybe you do that next time you get married.

24
00:01:09,280 --> 00:01:12,660
No, no, no. The next time's gonna be Hawaii at sunset.

25
00:01:13,620 --> 00:01:15,410
But maybe the time after that.

26
00:01:16,640 --> 00:01:18,730
《老友记》第十季第七集  领养中心来家访

27
00:01:56,390 --> 00:01:58,880
- Hey. What's going on? - Hey.

28
00:01:59,020 --> 00:02:01,310
Our adoption social worker is coming,

29
00:02:01,360 --> 00:02:02,890
so we're cleaning the apartment.

30
00:02:02,940 --> 00:02:03,950
"We"?

31
00:02:05,230 --> 00:02:07,160
You know you don't want me to help.

32
00:02:07,210 --> 00:02:09,140
You can't have it both ways.

33
00:02:10,550 --> 00:02:11,920
Is this the person who decides

34
00:02:11,970 --> 00:02:13,310
whether or not you get a baby?

35
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:16,000
Kind of. She's coming by to interview us and see where we live.

36
00:02:16,050 --> 00:02:17,370
And it has to go perfectly,

37
00:02:17,420 --> 00:02:18,980
because if she doesn't like something about us

38
00:02:19,030 --> 00:02:20,060
she can keep us off

39
00:02:20,060 --> 00:02:21,430
every adoption list in the state.

40
00:02:21,480 --> 00:02:22,810
Hey, maybe I should stop by.

41
00:02:22,920 --> 00:02:24,340
She could be a soap opera fan.

42
00:02:25,190 --> 00:02:26,220
It's very impressive

43
00:02:26,270 --> 00:02:27,950
when the little people know a celebrity.

44
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:30,820
"Little people"?

45
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:32,200
"Celebrity."

46
00:02:34,010 --> 00:02:35,540
So I think I'm just about done here.

47
00:02:35,590 --> 00:02:38,600
Unless you have any bad stuff hidden somewhere,

48
00:02:38,650 --> 00:02:40,710
like porn or cigarettes?

49
00:02:41,110 --> 00:02:42,110
What?

50
00:02:43,780 --> 00:02:46,030
- No. - Chandler.

51
00:02:49,130 --> 00:02:50,100
I don't,

52
00:02:50,150 --> 00:02:52,200
and I'm offended by the insinuation.

53
00:02:52,250 --> 00:02:55,800
So there's not a magazine under the couch...

54
00:02:55,850 --> 00:02:59,050
...or cigarettes taped to the back of the toilet tank...

55
00:02:59,100 --> 00:03:01,370
...or a filthy video in the VCR?

56
00:03:02,710 --> 00:03:04,450
I'll admit to the cigarettes and magazine.

57
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:06,180
But that tape is not mine.

58
00:03:06,570 --> 00:03:07,820
It isn't mine.

59
00:03:07,870 --> 00:03:09,640
I guess we'll never know whose it is.

60
00:03:18,340 --> 00:03:19,220
May I help you?

61
00:03:19,270 --> 00:03:20,450
Yes. We're here

62
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:23,130
to make a rather sizable donation to the children.

63
00:03:23,180 --> 00:03:24,840
Any contribution, large or small,

64
00:03:24,890 --> 00:03:25,840
is appreciated.

65
00:03:25,890 --> 00:03:27,230
I think you're gonna appreciate

66
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,680
the crap out of this one.

67
00:03:29,620 --> 00:03:31,150
Well, this is very generous.

68
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,830
And we don't want any recognition.

69
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:34,720
This is completely anonymous.

70
00:03:34,770 --> 00:03:37,390
Completely anonymous. From two kind strangers.

71
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:39,900
Mr. X and Phoebe Buffay.

72
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:42,420
Well if you like,

73
00:03:42,470 --> 00:03:43,840
we can include your names in our newsletter.

74
00:03:43,890 --> 00:03:44,700
Not necessary.

75
00:03:44,750 --> 00:03:46,920
Buffay is spelled B-U-F-F-A-Y.

76
00:03:48,050 --> 00:03:51,500
And X is spelled "Mike Hannigan."

77
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:55,770
Well, on behalf of the children, thank you both very much.

78
00:03:55,770 --> 00:03:58,340
I'm glad we did this. It feels so good.

79
00:03:58,390 --> 00:03:59,860
It does. It feels really good.

80
00:04:00,710 --> 00:04:02,650
Oh, look. And we get these free T-shirts.

81
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:05,360
Actually, that's the shirt I wore to the gym.

82
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,680
It's moist.

83
00:04:11,730 --> 00:04:13,680
Hi. Emma will be up in a minute.

84
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:14,550
Oh, good.

85
00:04:14,550 --> 00:04:17,720
Hey, Ross, listen. I heard about you and Charlie.

86
00:04:17,770 --> 00:04:18,660
I'm really sorry.

87
00:04:18,710 --> 00:04:20,040
That's okay.

88
00:04:20,090 --> 00:04:23,340
I'm sure there are tons of other beautiful paleontologists out there.

89
00:04:23,390 --> 00:04:24,260
Absolutely.

90
00:04:24,310 --> 00:04:26,310
There was one. She's it.

91
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:29,380
All the rest look like they should live under a bridge.

92
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:34,080
So, what are you gonna do today?

93
00:04:34,130 --> 00:04:36,440
I was thinking of taking Emma to the playground.

94
00:04:36,490 --> 00:04:38,430
Oh, my God. What?

95
00:04:40,510 --> 00:04:41,900
Like I said, I was thinking of

96
00:04:41,950 --> 00:04:45,210
taking Emma to the Museum of Knives and Fire.

97
00:04:47,660 --> 00:04:49,050
Okay, look, Ross.

98
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:52,970
I do not want Emma going to the playground.

99
00:04:56,730 --> 00:04:57,960
Because...?

100
00:04:58,010 --> 00:05:01,390
All right, if you must know, I had a traumatic...

101
00:05:01,930 --> 00:05:04,900
...swing incident when I was little.

102
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:08,530
- Seriously? - Yes. I was 4 years old.

103
00:05:08,580 --> 00:05:10,250
And I was on the swing...

104
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:14,430
...and then all of a sudden my hair got tangled in the chain.

105
00:05:16,050 --> 00:05:16,980
And to get me out,

106
00:05:17,030 --> 00:05:20,120
my mom had to cut a big chunk of my hair.

107
00:05:22,340 --> 00:05:24,700
And it was uneven for weeks.

108
00:05:31,190 --> 00:05:33,200
And you made it through that?

109
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:37,910
I wonder who's gonna play you in the movie.

110
00:05:39,650 --> 00:05:41,270
Okay, fine, you can make fun of me.

111
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:43,420
I do not want Emma going there.

112
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:45,940
Claire Danes:美剧《国家安全》女主角

113
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:45,940
And I was thinking Claire Danes.

114
00:05:47,230 --> 00:05:49,970
Look, I'm sorry to hear about your tragedy.

115
00:05:50,020 --> 00:05:52,220
But the swings are perfectly safe.

116
00:05:52,270 --> 00:05:53,720
And besides, Emma loves them.

117
00:05:53,770 --> 00:05:55,720
You should come, and you'll see.

118
00:05:55,770 --> 00:05:58,530
Those things go, like, 40 miles an hour.

119
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:00,780
And there's that moment when you're at the top...

120
00:06:00,830 --> 00:06:05,160
...when you just don't know if you're gonna return back to Earth.

121
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:09,900
Space is filled with orbiting children.

122
00:06:12,990 --> 00:06:15,540
Look, please, just come on.

123
00:06:15,590 --> 00:06:17,750
When you see the look on Emma's face,

124
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:19,170
I swear, you won't regret it.

125
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:23,250
- All right. - Good.

126
00:06:23,300 --> 00:06:24,900
You don't wanna be a mom

127
00:06:24,950 --> 00:06:28,090
who passes her irrational fears to her children.

128
00:06:28,140 --> 00:06:29,670
"Irrational," huh?

129
00:06:29,950 --> 00:06:31,690
I'll remember that next time

130
00:06:31,740 --> 00:06:33,540
you freak out about a spider in your apartment.

131
00:06:33,590 --> 00:06:35,460
That's the same. I'm sure there are 30

132
00:06:35,510 --> 00:06:37,770
different species of poisonous swings.

133
00:06:42,290 --> 00:06:44,570
Oh, my God. The adoption lady is early.

134
00:06:44,620 --> 00:06:47,610
Okay. Okay. Here we go. Here we go.

135
00:06:48,050 --> 00:06:49,320
Stand up straight.

136
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:50,940
Big smile.

137
00:06:53,860 --> 00:06:56,250
Hello. Is this the Creepy residence?

138
00:06:57,180 --> 00:06:58,930
We're waiting for the adoption lady.

139
00:06:58,980 --> 00:07:00,190
But I'm glad you're here.

140
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,750
I was cleaning this morning

141
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,250
and I found this.

142
00:07:03,580 --> 00:07:06,000
I don't know if you wanna use it, but....

143
00:07:06,570 --> 00:07:09,650
Oh, this is so sweet of you.

144
00:07:09,760 --> 00:07:10,880
But you know what?

145
00:07:10,880 --> 00:07:12,000
I won't be needing a veil,

146
00:07:12,050 --> 00:07:13,760
I actually won't be wearing a dress at all!

147
00:07:13,810 --> 00:07:14,520
I told you,

148
00:07:14,570 --> 00:07:16,490
I am not coming to a naked wedding!

149
00:07:16,980 --> 00:07:19,370
No. We're not having a big reception.

150
00:07:19,420 --> 00:07:21,240
we took the money we were gonna spend on a wedding

151
00:07:21,290 --> 00:07:23,310
and we donate them to the children charity.

152
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:24,920
That's crazy!

153
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:29,660
I'm sorry. I can't imagine giving up

154
00:07:29,660 --> 00:07:31,340
my one wedding day like that.

155
00:07:31,460 --> 00:07:32,700
Well, we're different.

156
00:07:32,740 --> 00:07:34,960
I don't care about having a huge party.

157
00:07:35,010 --> 00:07:37,410
This is really nice for you, but....

158
00:07:37,460 --> 00:07:41,170
Oh, please. I put this on and I just look like--

159
00:07:41,220 --> 00:07:42,420
Well, radiant.

160
00:07:45,350 --> 00:07:46,710
All right, but who cares?

161
00:07:46,760 --> 00:07:49,470
I don't need a pretty veil and a fancy dress.

162
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:51,810
That's right. You're making a commitment.

163
00:07:51,860 --> 00:07:55,010
You know, that's the same whether you do it at the Plaza or....

164
00:07:55,060 --> 00:07:57,230
- Where you gonna do it? - City Hall.

165
00:07:57,280 --> 00:08:01,480
Oh, that sounds nice.

166
00:08:02,300 --> 00:08:03,980
I was just there for jury duty.

167
00:08:04,030 --> 00:08:06,110
They've really spruced that place up.

168
00:08:06,610 --> 00:08:08,010
Okay. It's okay...

169
00:08:08,060 --> 00:08:11,120
I've made my decision.

170
00:08:11,420 --> 00:08:14,200
What I really want is a great big wedding.

171
00:08:16,460 --> 00:08:18,730
But you gave all the money to charity.

172
00:08:18,780 --> 00:08:20,540
Well, I'll just ask for it back.

173
00:08:22,330 --> 00:08:23,740
I don't think you can do that.

174
00:08:23,790 --> 00:08:24,710
Why not?

175
00:08:24,760 --> 00:08:25,630
This is her wedding day.

176
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:28,760
That's way more important than some stupid kids.

177
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:31,290
That's sweet, honey,

178
00:08:31,340 --> 00:08:33,460
but save something for the adoption lady.

179
00:08:40,350 --> 00:08:42,710
- All right, okay. Be careful. - Okay.

180
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:45,750
Careful. Watch her hair. Watch her hair!

181
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:49,330
Rach, she's got, like, three hairs.

182
00:08:49,380 --> 00:08:50,820
I know. I know.

183
00:08:50,870 --> 00:08:52,730
But they're just so beautiful.

184
00:08:52,780 --> 00:08:54,960
Oh, my God, I just pulled one out.

185
00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:57,600
I promise you she's safe.

186
00:08:57,650 --> 00:08:59,730
Watch how much she loves this.

187
00:08:59,780 --> 00:09:00,520
Okay. Okay.

188
00:09:00,570 --> 00:09:02,930
Are you ready, sweetie? Here we go.

189
00:09:04,490 --> 00:09:07,430
Okay, careful. Okay.

190
00:09:11,620 --> 00:09:13,330
She's smiling.

191
00:09:13,950 --> 00:09:16,140
Look at that, she does like it.

192
00:09:16,260 --> 00:09:17,960
See, I told you.

193
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:24,350
Oh, my God.

194
00:09:24,350 --> 00:09:26,970
Look at her, she's a little daredevil.

195
00:09:27,190 --> 00:09:29,430
Oh, God. Let me push. Can I push?

196
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:31,280
Oh, absolutely.

197
00:09:31,740 --> 00:09:33,830
Oh, God. Okay, get the camera.

198
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:35,330
It's in the diaper bag.

199
00:09:35,380 --> 00:09:36,480
Okay.

200
00:09:37,140 --> 00:09:39,460
See? Scared of the swings.

201
00:09:39,460 --> 00:09:41,000
I bet you feel pretty silly.

202
00:09:46,070 --> 00:09:48,140
We're asking for the money back?

203
00:09:48,190 --> 00:09:49,700
It's for our wedding day.

204
00:09:49,750 --> 00:09:51,850
Now, is this guy gay or straight?

205
00:09:51,900 --> 00:09:54,020
Because one of us has to start flirting.

206
00:09:55,620 --> 00:09:57,910
You here to make another donation the same day?

207
00:09:57,960 --> 00:09:59,850
I don't think that's ever happened before.

208
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:01,330
Gay. Go.

209
00:10:04,790 --> 00:10:06,750
Oh, my God, I love your shirt.

210
00:10:08,950 --> 00:10:10,990
The donation we made earlier?

211
00:10:11,040 --> 00:10:13,560
Well, we want it back.

212
00:10:14,940 --> 00:10:15,860
Excuse me?

213
00:10:15,910 --> 00:10:18,620
Okay, that money was for a big wedding

214
00:10:18,670 --> 00:10:19,860
we thought we didn't want.

215
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:21,360
But it turns out we do.

216
00:10:21,410 --> 00:10:22,700
So you're asking us

217
00:10:22,750 --> 00:10:24,970
to refund your donation to the children?

218
00:10:25,350 --> 00:10:26,240
Yeah.

219
00:10:28,170 --> 00:10:29,660
This feels really good.

220
00:10:33,740 --> 00:10:35,510
I'm sorry. I am.

221
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:37,590
But this wedding's just really important to me.

222
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:39,310
Hey, it's none of my business.

223
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:41,550
Besides, this is probably a good thing.

224
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:43,210
We've really been spoiling the children,

225
00:10:43,260 --> 00:10:45,160
what with all the food and warm clothing.

226
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:48,330
That's not fair.

227
00:10:48,380 --> 00:10:50,090
A person's wedding is important.

228
00:10:50,140 --> 00:10:51,820
And especially to me.

229
00:10:51,870 --> 00:10:54,340
I didn't have a graduation party.

230
00:10:54,390 --> 00:10:55,820
And I didn't go to prom.

231
00:10:55,870 --> 00:10:59,880
And I spent my sweet 16 being chased around a tire yard...

232
00:10:59,930 --> 00:11:02,260
...by an escaped mental patient

233
00:11:02,310 --> 00:11:03,650
who, in his own words, wanted to:

234
00:11:03,700 --> 00:11:05,210
"Kill me, or whatever."

235
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:10,020
So I deserve a real celebration.

236
00:11:10,070 --> 00:11:12,960
And I'm not gonna let some sweaty little man

237
00:11:13,010 --> 00:11:14,810
make me feel badly about it.

238
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:21,110
She could've been talking about either one of us.

239
00:11:28,030 --> 00:11:29,230
Hi, I'm Laura.

240
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:30,960
I'm here for your adoption interview.

241
00:11:31,010 --> 00:11:33,690
Hi, I'm Monica. And this is Chandler.

242
00:11:33,810 --> 00:11:36,090
- Please come in. - Thank you.

243
00:11:36,220 --> 00:11:37,600
Would you like something to drink?

244
00:11:37,650 --> 00:11:38,860
Water would be fine.

245
00:11:38,910 --> 00:11:41,580
We're so glad that you're here.

246
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:44,740
We're excited about getting this process started.

247
00:11:44,790 --> 00:11:47,290
Because we love kids. Love them to death.

248
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:49,820
Well, not actually to death.

249
00:11:49,870 --> 00:11:51,460
That's just a figure of speech.

250
00:11:51,510 --> 00:11:53,550
We love kids the appropriate amount...

251
00:11:55,300 --> 00:11:57,210
...as allowed by law.

252
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:01,940
- Your place is just lovely. - Thank you.

253
00:12:01,990 --> 00:12:04,660
Yes, this building does have a wholesome,

254
00:12:04,660 --> 00:12:05,900
family feel to it.

255
00:12:06,070 --> 00:12:08,560
I feel like I've been here before.

256
00:12:08,610 --> 00:12:10,660
Any other couples in the building adopting?

257
00:12:10,710 --> 00:12:12,490
Is that that couple on the first floor?

258
00:12:12,540 --> 00:12:14,750
Because we should get a baby before them.

259
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:17,290
That guy tried to sell me drugs.

260
00:12:18,630 --> 00:12:20,130
But other than that,

261
00:12:20,130 --> 00:12:21,810
wholesome, wholesome building.

262
00:12:24,690 --> 00:12:25,450
What?

263
00:12:25,670 --> 00:12:28,300
I realized why I remember this place.

264
00:12:28,350 --> 00:12:29,500
Really? What is it?

265
00:12:29,550 --> 00:12:30,530
Oh, it's nothing.

266
00:12:30,580 --> 00:12:32,360
I went on a date with a guy who lived in this building.

267
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:34,440
It didn't end very well.

268
00:12:34,860 --> 00:12:38,190
That wouldn't, by any chance, be Joey Tribbiani?

269
00:12:38,230 --> 00:12:40,850
- Yes! - Of course it was.

270
00:12:41,950 --> 00:12:43,690
We had a great night.

271
00:12:43,690 --> 00:12:45,240
In the morning, he promised he'd call

272
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:46,320
and he didn't.

273
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:48,190
Rat bastard!

274
00:12:50,070 --> 00:12:51,070
So you're not friends with him?

275
00:12:51,070 --> 00:12:52,000
Oh, God, no.

276
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,210
No, no, no.

277
00:12:53,210 --> 00:12:54,740
No. Nope.

278
00:12:54,740 --> 00:12:55,600
No...

279
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:56,280
No...

280
00:12:56,280 --> 00:12:57,020
No...

281
00:12:57,020 --> 00:12:57,650
No...

282
00:12:59,240 --> 00:12:59,870
No...

283
00:13:02,550 --> 00:13:04,740
Well, I'm sorry I brought it up.

284
00:13:04,740 --> 00:13:08,110
So are either one of you planning on staying at home?

285
00:13:08,290 --> 00:13:12,680
Hello? Anybody in there order a celebrity?

286
00:13:16,380 --> 00:13:17,870
What was that?

287
00:13:17,870 --> 00:13:20,860
That's just some crazy guy who roams the halls here.

288
00:13:21,690 --> 00:13:23,650
He's great with kids, though.

289
00:13:30,660 --> 00:13:33,080
Ross. Oh, my God, are you okay?

290
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:34,700
Son of a bitch!

291
00:13:38,830 --> 00:13:41,530
Oh, relax. I didn't say the F-word.

292
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:44,450
Ross, see,

293
00:13:44,450 --> 00:13:46,810
I told you! Those swings are evil!

294
00:13:46,860 --> 00:13:48,130
That is it.

295
00:13:48,180 --> 00:13:49,710
That's the last time Emma is getting on

296
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:51,570
one of those things for her entire life.

297
00:13:51,690 --> 00:13:54,310
No, no, no. Okay, it wasn't the swing's fault.

298
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:55,630
It was my fault.

299
00:13:55,680 --> 00:13:57,970
And kind of that kid's fault.

300
00:13:58,630 --> 00:14:01,660
Who is still laughing. Nice.

301
00:14:02,140 --> 00:14:04,050
Come on. Can we just get out of here

302
00:14:04,100 --> 00:14:05,600
before somebody else gets hurt?

303
00:14:05,650 --> 00:14:07,580
No. Wait. Ok, ok. I have an idea.

304
00:14:07,630 --> 00:14:09,220
I want you to get on the swing...

305
00:14:09,270 --> 00:14:12,660
...and you'll see that there's nothing to be afraid of.

306
00:14:15,270 --> 00:14:17,120
I know what this is all about.

307
00:14:18,210 --> 00:14:20,440
You've always been jealous of my hair.

308
00:14:21,700 --> 00:14:23,900
I just think you're an adult, okay?

309
00:14:23,950 --> 00:14:26,040
And you should get over your silly fears.

310
00:14:26,090 --> 00:14:28,080
All right, fine. I'll do it.

311
00:14:28,130 --> 00:14:28,730
Good.

312
00:14:28,780 --> 00:14:29,810
If you hold a spider.

313
00:14:29,860 --> 00:14:31,200
Where?! Where?!

314
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:34,630
If you hold a spider.

315
00:14:35,030 --> 00:14:36,130
I know.

316
00:14:43,750 --> 00:14:45,360
Guys, is everything okay?

317
00:14:45,510 --> 00:14:46,940
It's me, Joey.

318
00:14:49,150 --> 00:14:50,600
Adoption!

319
00:14:52,750 --> 00:14:53,920
What's going on?

320
00:14:54,040 --> 00:14:56,540
Oh, it's just like I said, that crazy...

321
00:14:57,130 --> 00:14:59,930
...Bert, roaming the halls.

322
00:15:00,880 --> 00:15:01,630
Guys?

323
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:03,160
Keep on roaming, Bert!

324
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:07,140
We don't want any crazy today!

325
00:15:07,610 --> 00:15:08,580
What's going on?

326
00:15:08,580 --> 00:15:11,150
We'll talk later! Bert. Everything's fine!

327
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:14,240
Everything doesn't sound fine.

328
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:16,890
Is he all right out there by himself?

329
00:15:16,890 --> 00:15:18,340
Oh, yeah. He has a caretaker.

330
00:15:18,340 --> 00:15:19,660
His older brother...

331
00:15:20,770 --> 00:15:22,240
...Ernie.

332
00:15:24,580 --> 00:15:26,060
Bert and Ernie?

333
00:15:24,580 --> 00:15:26,060
Bert and Ernie:《芝麻街》里的动画角色

334
00:15:26,060 --> 00:15:28,460
You can't make this stuff up.

335
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:31,780
You never told me about that guy

336
00:15:31,780 --> 00:15:33,290
and your sweet 16.

337
00:15:33,290 --> 00:15:34,820
I'm sorry about that.

338
00:15:34,820 --> 00:15:36,360
Oh, it ended okay.

339
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:38,210
One of my friends shot him.

340
00:15:40,150 --> 00:15:42,760
At least you'll get a proper wedding.

341
00:15:42,760 --> 00:15:43,750
You really deserve that.

342
00:15:43,750 --> 00:15:45,210
Yeah, I really do.

343
00:15:45,210 --> 00:15:47,410
You know, I had nothing growing up.

344
00:15:50,150 --> 00:15:52,610
Just like the kids I took the money from.

345
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:55,660
No... I see where this is going.

346
00:15:55,660 --> 00:15:57,620
Don't make me go back there.

347
00:15:58,880 --> 00:16:01,640
Look, I can't have a wedding with this money now.

348
00:16:01,690 --> 00:16:02,890
It's tainted.

349
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:05,830
Fine, we'll give the money back.

350
00:16:05,880 --> 00:16:07,100
If that guy at the charity

351
00:16:07,150 --> 00:16:08,310
gives us a hard time...

352
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:11,510
...my friend hasn't shot anyone in a really long time.

353
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:15,250
I must say this seems like

354
00:16:15,250 --> 00:16:17,100
a lovely environment to raise a child in.

355
00:16:17,150 --> 00:16:19,380
You are welcome to look under

356
00:16:19,380 --> 00:16:20,370
any of the furniture...

357
00:16:20,420 --> 00:16:21,430
...because, believe me,

358
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:23,840
you won't find any porn or cigarettes under there.

359
00:16:24,930 --> 00:16:26,450
Before we look around,

360
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:27,820
let me make sure

361
00:16:27,820 --> 00:16:28,860
I have everything I need up to here.

362
00:16:35,170 --> 00:16:37,330
Why don't I show you the baby's room.

363
00:16:42,610 --> 00:16:43,920
What are you doing?

364
00:16:43,970 --> 00:16:44,920
You wouldn't let me in.

365
00:16:44,970 --> 00:16:46,160
I thought you were in trouble.

366
00:16:46,210 --> 00:16:47,040
Well, we're not.

367
00:16:47,090 --> 00:16:48,410
But you called me "Bert."

368
00:16:50,110 --> 00:16:51,930
That's our code word for danger.

369
00:16:53,340 --> 00:16:55,240
We don't have a code word.

370
00:16:55,290 --> 00:16:55,980
We don't?

371
00:16:57,430 --> 00:16:58,550
We really should.

372
00:16:59,180 --> 00:16:59,990
From now on,

373
00:17:00,040 --> 00:17:02,520
"Bert" will be our code word for danger.

374
00:17:03,280 --> 00:17:05,520
So that was the baby's room.

375
00:17:07,560 --> 00:17:09,120
What room should we see next?

376
00:17:09,170 --> 00:17:11,420
Any room that isn't behind this couch.

377
00:17:13,830 --> 00:17:15,310
Some people don't get him,

378
00:17:15,360 --> 00:17:17,080
but I think he's really funny.

379
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:26,690
I did not care for that.

380
00:17:28,380 --> 00:17:29,580
You have to leave.

381
00:17:29,630 --> 00:17:31,330
You slept with our social worker

382
00:17:31,380 --> 00:17:32,510
and never called her back.

383
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:33,630
She is still pissed,

384
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:34,670
so she can't see you.

385
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:36,200
Okay, okay.

386
00:17:39,540 --> 00:17:41,950
- What? - I forgot my bat.

387
00:17:45,100 --> 00:17:46,700
Oh, my God.

388
00:17:47,310 --> 00:17:48,580
And for the last time,

389
00:17:48,630 --> 00:17:51,130
we do not want to be friends with you!

390
00:17:53,720 --> 00:17:55,660
And we don't wanna buy your bat!

391
00:17:57,970 --> 00:17:59,620
What are you doing here?

392
00:17:59,940 --> 00:18:01,790
Bert...

393
00:18:06,270 --> 00:18:07,660
Are you friends with him?

394
00:18:07,710 --> 00:18:08,900
I can explain.

395
00:18:10,410 --> 00:18:11,410
Joey?

396
00:18:12,780 --> 00:18:14,230
All right. Okay.

397
00:18:18,860 --> 00:18:22,460
You have got some nerve coming back here.

398
00:18:23,390 --> 00:18:25,190
I can't believe you never called me.

399
00:18:25,190 --> 00:18:26,980
Excuse me?

400
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:29,050
You probably don't even remember my name.

401
00:18:29,050 --> 00:18:30,650
It's Joey, by the way.

402
00:18:30,650 --> 00:18:31,820
And don't bother telling me yours,

403
00:18:31,820 --> 00:18:34,910
because I totally remember it, lady.

404
00:18:38,070 --> 00:18:39,600
I waited weeks for you to call me.

405
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:40,680
I gave you my number.

406
00:18:40,680 --> 00:18:41,690
You never called me.

407
00:18:41,740 --> 00:18:43,790
Don't try to turn this around on me.

408
00:18:43,840 --> 00:18:47,930
I am not some kind of social work...

409
00:18:47,980 --> 00:18:49,900
...that you can just...

410
00:18:49,950 --> 00:18:51,050
...do.

411
00:18:54,510 --> 00:18:56,970
I'm pretty sure I gave you my number.

412
00:18:57,020 --> 00:18:59,140
Really? Think about it. Come on.

413
00:18:59,190 --> 00:19:00,810
You're a beautiful woman.

414
00:19:00,860 --> 00:19:02,430
Smart, funny.

415
00:19:02,840 --> 00:19:04,990
We had a really good time.

416
00:19:06,860 --> 00:19:07,900
If I had your number,

417
00:19:07,950 --> 00:19:09,160
why wouldn't I call you?

418
00:19:10,170 --> 00:19:11,180
I don't know.

419
00:19:13,370 --> 00:19:14,630
Well, maybe I'm wrong.

420
00:19:14,680 --> 00:19:15,370
I'm sorry.

421
00:19:15,420 --> 00:19:19,030
Hey, too late for apologies. Okay?

422
00:19:19,080 --> 00:19:20,690
You broke my heart.

423
00:19:20,740 --> 00:19:21,670
You know how many women

424
00:19:21,720 --> 00:19:22,980
I had to sleep with to get over you?

425
00:19:27,420 --> 00:19:29,070
- Joey, wait-- - No!

426
00:19:29,740 --> 00:19:30,800
I waited a long time!

427
00:19:30,850 --> 00:19:32,150
I can't wait anymore.

428
00:19:36,120 --> 00:19:38,150
I'm sorry that you had to see that.

429
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:39,170
I'm so embarrassed.

430
00:19:39,220 --> 00:19:40,460
Oh, that's really okay.

431
00:19:40,510 --> 00:19:42,690
Yeah. We totally understand.

432
00:19:42,740 --> 00:19:44,080
Dating is hard.

433
00:19:44,580 --> 00:19:46,400
Boy, you people are nice.

434
00:19:48,050 --> 00:19:49,610
And I've got to say...

435
00:19:49,970 --> 00:19:53,220
...l think you're going to make excellent parents.

436
00:19:57,250 --> 00:19:58,620
Laura!

437
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:07,070
We're back.

438
00:20:08,630 --> 00:20:10,280
Are you here to take more money?

439
00:20:11,190 --> 00:20:13,550
Because I think what you're looking for is an ATM.

440
00:20:14,460 --> 00:20:16,630
No, no, we're here to give the money back.

441
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:18,370
Yeah. Because you know what?

442
00:20:19,060 --> 00:20:20,770
It's all about the children.

443
00:20:20,820 --> 00:20:23,570
Although it's also about the wedding.

444
00:20:24,830 --> 00:20:25,910
All right, here.

445
00:20:26,010 --> 00:20:27,390
No. Oh, God.

446
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:28,930
If I haven't said so already,

447
00:20:28,980 --> 00:20:30,560
sir, congratulations.

448
00:20:31,860 --> 00:20:33,910
Enough, all right?

449
00:20:33,910 --> 00:20:35,910
I'm stepping in and putting my foot down.

450
00:20:35,960 --> 00:20:36,740
As your future husband,

451
00:20:36,740 --> 00:20:39,470
I'm gonna make this decision for us.

452
00:20:40,540 --> 00:20:43,010
What do you think we should do?

453
00:20:43,770 --> 00:20:46,450
You know what. It's not your decision anymore.

454
00:20:46,450 --> 00:20:47,080
What?

455
00:20:47,080 --> 00:20:48,770
On behalf of the children of New York,

456
00:20:48,770 --> 00:20:50,540
I reject your money.

457
00:20:51,410 --> 00:20:52,730
But we're giving you this.

458
00:20:52,730 --> 00:20:54,440
And I'm giving it back to you.

459
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:57,000
Come on. Consider it a contribution.

460
00:20:58,650 --> 00:21:00,890
Well, this is very generous.

461
00:21:01,560 --> 00:21:02,610
Please take the check.

462
00:21:02,610 --> 00:21:03,600
Have a great wedding

463
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:05,670
and a wonderful life together.

464
00:21:05,750 --> 00:21:07,200
Sounds good to me.

465
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:09,100
We can save up, come back in a few years...

466
00:21:09,100 --> 00:21:10,400
...and make an even bigger donation.

467
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:13,150
Absolutely. And when you do, make sure you ask for Brian.

468
00:21:13,150 --> 00:21:14,940
- Oh, is that you? - No.

469
00:21:20,420 --> 00:21:21,300
Hello?

470
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:23,870
Oh, hi.

471
00:21:25,440 --> 00:21:27,630
Oh, my God, really?

472
00:21:27,680 --> 00:21:29,480
I can't wait to tell Chandler.

473
00:21:29,530 --> 00:21:30,870
Okay. Goodbye.

474
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:32,970
Wrong number?

475
00:21:33,750 --> 00:21:34,940
That was Laura.

476
00:21:35,580 --> 00:21:36,900
She gave us a great report

477
00:21:36,950 --> 00:21:38,890
and we're officially on the waiting list.

478
00:21:38,940 --> 00:21:39,840
That's great.

479
00:21:39,890 --> 00:21:40,970
Now we just wait for a call...

480
00:21:41,020 --> 00:21:42,350
...and someone tells us

481
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:44,060
there's a baby waiting for us.

482
00:21:57,500 --> 00:21:58,430
Hello?

483
00:21:59,580 --> 00:22:00,940
Have you seen Joey's bat?

484
00:22:07,550 --> 00:22:10,200
Okay. I got a spider.

485
00:22:10,590 --> 00:22:12,420
There were two, I picked the bigger one.

486
00:22:14,140 --> 00:22:16,000
- Okay. - Okay.

487
00:22:20,070 --> 00:22:22,330
This feels perfectly normal.

488
00:22:23,360 --> 00:22:25,160
Okay, get on the swing.

489
00:22:27,640 --> 00:22:28,920
Okay.

490
00:22:30,190 --> 00:22:32,590
Okay.

491
00:22:38,260 --> 00:22:39,240
Okay.

492
00:22:47,230 --> 00:22:48,120
See?

493
00:22:48,170 --> 00:22:50,400
All right. I can do this.

494
00:22:50,450 --> 00:22:52,460
There you go. Good for you.

495
00:22:52,510 --> 00:22:54,910
You know what? I'm getting used to this little guy.

496
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:57,330
I don't even feel him in here anymore.

497
00:22:57,380 --> 00:22:58,990
That's because he's on your neck.

